<HEADLINE>
<P>
CRISTIANI'S PLEA FOR CONTINUED MILITARY AID 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It was a shock to see the commentary by President Cristiani. The numbers killed 
by the military totally ignored, no recognition of the concrete changes vitally 
needed, no mention of the tremendous support of the population for an end to 
military impunity and petitions for meaningful negotiations, no statement of 
wages frozen since 1980, no comment about the bombing of crops and civilian 
communities in rural areas when combat with guerrillas are miles away, no plans 
for education, no program for medical care regardless of political perspective, 
no realization of land issues, no plan for freedom to move within the country 
or of association. 
</P>
<P>
LYNNE HALPIN, Chair, Central America/Caribbean Committee, United Methodist 
Board of Church &amp; Society, Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
