<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: ARTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mapplethorpe Foundation Donates to AIDS Group: A foundation established by the 
late photographer Robert Mapplethorpe has pledged a $3-million donation to the 
American Foundation for AIDS research to be used over a three-year period. The 
money will come primarily from the sale of his photographs, some of which were 
put on trial in Cincinnati in the unusual obscenity case that ended in 
acquittals Friday for the art gallery and its director. The artist died of AIDS 
last year. CLAUDIA PUIG 
</P>
