<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: YORBA LINDA; 
</P>
<P>
5-ACRE PARK OKD BY CITY COUNCIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council has approved a plan to build a 5-acre park on the city's 
rapidly growing east side. 
</P>
<P>
The $500,000 park, to be located at Paseo de Toronto near Bryant Ranch 
Elementary School, will include a picnic area, gazebo, barbecue pits, a lighted 
basketball court, two lighted tennis courts and playground equipment. 
</P>
<P>
In addition, the park plan incorporates a baseball diamond and soccer field 
already constructed next to Bryant Ranch School at 24695 Paseo de Toronto. 
</P>
<P>
Yorba Linda's Parks and Recreation Department recommended to the City Council 
that a provision be made to consider lighting the baseball field. 
</P>
