<P>
COVINA FIRM'S BID WINS STREET CONTRACT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Fullerton City Council has hired a Covina-based construction company to 
finish the Euclid Street improvement project. 
</P>
<P>
The council accepted the bid of $1.7 million by Aman Brothers Inc., which was 
16% higher than the city originally had estimated, but the lowest bid received. 
</P>
<P>
The $2-million project, between Malvern Avenue and Bastanchury Road, will add 
additional sidewalks and install left-turn lanes. The project is expected to be 
completed by summer of next year. 
