<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: IRVINE; 
</P>
<P>
RESTAURANT MANAGER IS BEATEN BY ROBBERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The manager of an El Pollo Loco restaurant was struck repeatedly with a 
baseball bat when he was unable to open a safe quickly enough for a band of 
robbers, Irvine police said. 
</P>
<P>
Four men wearing ski masks and gloves and armed with knives and the bat entered 
the restaurant, at 88 Corporate Park, at 12:25 a.m. Sunday through the front 
door, Police Sgt. Tom Little said. 
</P>
<P>
They confronted manager Mariano Perez, 30, of Laguna Niguel and employee Jose 
Rodriguez, 24, of Santa Ana and demanded a key to the safe. 
</P>
<P>
When he was unable to open the safe, one suspect struck Perez several times on 
the head and shoulders and demanded that he open it. But before Perez could 
comply, the suspect struck him several more times on his upper body. 
</P>
<P>
The suspects tied up the two employees with nylon cord, put them in a small 
locker room and fled with between $2,500 and $3,000. 
</P>
<P>
After 15 minutes, Perez and Rodriguez were able to free themselves and called 
police. 
</P>
<P>
They were treated at the scene by paramedics and taken to Irvine Medical 
Center. Both men were treated and released. 
</P>
</TEXT>
