<HEADLINE>
<P>
SUSPECTED DRUNK DRIVER CRASHES CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man suspected of drunk driving crashed into another car on the Santa Ana 
Freeway early Sunday, injuring himself and several others. 
</P>
<P>
A California Highway Patrol spokesman said that Jose Luis Saavedra, 25, of 
Santa Ana, suspected of being intoxicated, was driving north on the Santa Ana 
Freeway at a "high rate of speed" about 1 a.m. Sunday when he rear-ended 
another car north of the Main Street off-ramp in Tustin. 
</P>
<P>
The car, driven by Jay Shaver, 47, of Whittier, went out of control, hit a 
signpost and overturned down an embankment. Shaver was uninjured but an 
unidentified passenger sustained serious injuries and was taken to Western 
Medical Center-Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
Saavedra was taken to UCI Medical Center in Orange. His three passengers 
suffered minor injures. 
</P>
