<HEADLINE>
<P>
CASTS CHOSEN FOR BRITISH OPERA DATES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The D'Oyly Carte Opera Company of Great Britain has announced casting for "The 
Mikado" and "The Pirates of Penzance," Oct.16 through 21 at the Orange County 
Performing Arts Center in Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
* "The Mikado," Oct. 16 through 18, 8 p.m.: David Fieldsend will sing 
Nanki-Poo, Sandra Dugdale will appear as Yum-Yum, Eric Roberts will be Ko-Ko. 
</P>
<P>
Susan Gorton will sing Katisha. Michael Ducarel will be the Mikado. John Ayldon 
will appear as Pooh-Bah. John Pryce-Jones will conduct on Oct. 16 and 17; Tim 
Dean will take over on Oct. 18. 
</P>
<P>
The production will be staged by Christopher Webber. Sets are by Eileen Diss, 
costumes by Jessica Gwynne and lighting design by Paul Pyant. Carole Todd is 
the choreographer. 
</P>
<P>
* "Pirates," Oct. 19 through 21 at 8 p.m., and Oct. 20 and 21 at 2 p.m: 
Fieldsend will sing Frederic, and Marilyn Hill Smith will be Mabel. Roberts 
will appear as Major-General Stanley, Malcolm Rivers will be the Pirate King. 
Gorton will sing Ruth. John Rath will be the Police Sergeant. Pryce-Jones will 
conduct the evening performances; Dean will conduct the matinees. 
</P>
<P>
Keith Warner will direct. Virginia Mason is credited as reviving the staging. 
Sets and costumes are by Marie Jeanne Lecca. Lighting design is by Pyant and 
choreography by Anthony van Laast. 
</P>
<P>
Tickets: $12 to $39. Information: (714) 556-2787. 
</P>
</TEXT>
