<P>
YUGOSLAVIA; 
</P>
<P>
TOP SERBIAN PARTY SUSPENDS TALKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Serbia's ruling Communists suspended talks with the federal government on 
resolving ethnic tensions in Kosovo province, angered that two members of a 
federal delegation had met leaders of the ethnic Albanian majority. "The visit 
of the federal government delegation to Kosovo has been completed as far as I 
and the government of Serbia are concerned," said Serbian Vice President 
Momcilo Trajkovic, who has been overseeing Kosovo since the government of 
Yugoslavia's largest republic assumed direct control of the province on July. 
5. 
</P>
