speakers from the fledgling Radical Party, one of dozens of political 
organizations that have sprouted under President Mikhail S. Gorbachev's 
glasnost (openness) reforms, criticized the United States and the Soviet Union 
for the arms buildups and said the draft is now unnecessary. 
