<HEADLINE>
<P>
SYDNER'S BIG GAME SPARKS HAWAII, 44-3 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HONOLULU 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jeff Sydner scored four touchdowns and broke a school record for all-purpose 
yardage as Hawaii defeated Maine, 44-3, Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
Hawaii improved to 2-2, and the Black Bears, an NCAA Division I-AA team, fell 
to 0-5. 
</P>
<P>
Sydner, a sophomore slotback, rushed for 62 yards, caught passes for 87 yards, 
had 111 yards in punt returns and 12 yards in kickoff returns in amassing 272 
all-purpose yards. 
</P>
<P>
The former record of 270 yards was set by Rusty Holt in 1927 and tied by Pete 
Wilson in 1950. 
</P>
</TEXT>
