<HEADLINE>
<P>
12 KILLED -- 6 IN DRIVE-BY SHOOTINGS -- ON WEEKEND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At least 12 people were killed in weekend violence in the Los Angeles area, six 
in unrelated drive-by shootings, authorities said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
In one incident, four pedestrians were struck by bullets fired indiscriminately 
from a passing car about six blocks from the Los Angeles Memorial Coliseum, Los 
Angeles Police Sgt. David Young said. 
</P>
<P>
One of the men, a 22-year-old whose name was not released pending notification 
of relatives, died at 1 a.m. Sunday. The three other men were in stable 
condition at area hospitals. 
</P>
<P>
"As best as we can tell (the gunman) just started opening fire . . . shooting 
at anyone who was there," Young said of the shooting near 39th Street and 
Normandie Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
As with the other drive-by shootings, there were no arrests. 
</P>
<P>
Among the victims of other weekend violence was a 16-year-old Palmdale boy who 
died Saturday after he held a gun to his head and pulled the trigger, thinking 
it was unloaded, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Jason Sanders died instantly from a single shot to the head from the .44-magnum 
revolver, the coroner's office said. 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles County sheriff's deputies said the boy took the gun, which belongs 
to his mother's boyfriend, from his house about 10:30 p.m. He pointed it 
playfully at two friends and ordered them not to move before placing the barrel 
to his temple and firing, deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
The boyfriend left the gun out because he planned to go hunting Sunday morning, 
deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
In another incident, a sheriff's deputy shot at -- but missed -- a man who 
allegedly was firing his semiautomatic pistol into homes in his Florence-area 
neighborhood early Sunday. The suspect, Ballentine Gonzalez, 26, was arrested 
after a short struggle and was being held on suspicion of assault with a deadly 
weapon, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
A 17-year-old boy was stabbed and found bleeding to death in a driveway in the 
11200 block of El Rey Drive in Whittier, police said Sunday. The boy was 
believed to have been stabbed in a fight about two blocks away. 
</P>
<P>
In the other drive-by killings reported by authorities: 
</P>
<P>
* An unidentified 19-year-old was slain in front of a taco stand in East Los 
Angeles about 2 a.m. Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
* Jose Rodriguez, a 20-year-old suspected gang member, was struck and killed as 
he partied about 12:15 a.m. Sunday in the street in the Cypress Park area east 
of downtown. Party-goers, including gang members, were "very uncooperative 
witnesses," and did not provide a description of the gunman's car, Detective 
Ron Whitt said. 
</P>
<P>
* Edward Jaquez, 25, of San Pedro was killed as he stepped into the street in 
the 1000 block of South Center Street about 11:35 p.m. Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
* Also Saturday night, two men were hit by gunfire in South Los Angeles as they 
stood in front of a coin laundry at 7601 S. Vermont Ave. Delbert Bain, 29, who 
was shot in the back, died at Daniel Freeman Memorial Hospital, while the 
second victim was in serious condition with a jaw wound. 
</P>
<P>
* Danny Hurtado, 17, of Pomona, was killed late Friday when a passing gunman 
fired three shotgun volleys at him as he walked on East Grand Avenue in that 
city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
