<HEADLINE>
<P>
SUPPORT GROWS FOR A TAX TRADE; 
</P>
<P>
DEFICIT: AS TALKS WEAR ON, HOUSE REPUBLICANS ENDORSE A POSSIBLE COMPROMISE THAT 
WOULD RAISE RATES FOR RICH IN EXCHANGE FOR CUTS IN CAPITAL GAINS. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAUL HOUSTON and TOM REDBURN, TIMES STAFF WRITERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
