SHORT TAKES; 
</P>
<P>
CREATOR OF BETTY BOOP DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Myron (Grim) Natwick, the creator of the popular 60-year-old cartoon heroine 
Betty Boop, has died. 
</P>
<P>
He was 100. 
</P>
<P>
Natwick died Sunday at Santa Monica Hospital Medical Center of pneumonia and 
heart disease. 
</P>
<P>
"Although she was never vulgar or obscene, Betty was a suggestion you could 
spell in three letters: S-E-X," Natwick said of her enduring popularity in a 
Times interview earlier this year. "She was all girl." 
